-- Softbank, PayPal form Japan JV, target iPhone users
-- 
-- Wed May 9, 2012 1:41am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/05/09/us-softbank-paypal-idUSBRE84803Z20120509

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Softbank Corp said on Wednesday that it and eBay Inc unit PayPal will form a joint venture to expand Japan's e-payments market by targeting users of Apple Inc's iPhone. 
 Softbank, which competes with bigger KDDI Corp in supplying Apple's popular smartphone in Japan, and PayPal will each invest 1 billion yen ($12.54 million) in the joint venture, Softbank President Masayoshi Son told reporters at a news conference. (Reporting by Ayai Tomisawa)